{"version":"https://jsonfeed.org/version/1.1","title":"Toshiki's Devpedia","description":"Design, Build & Ship; Privacy, Security & Automation.","home_page_url":"https://tg.toshiki.dev/","feed_url":"https://tg.toshiki.dev/rss.json","items":[{"id":"https://tg.toshiki.dev/posts/520","url":"https://tg.toshiki.dev/posts/520","title":"Surprisingly, after tightening nearly every corner of the stack from static generation and CDN delivery to image optimization and caching; this actually turned out to be one of the fastest sites I’ve built so far. Seeing the performance audits and SEO scores come out this strong was genuinely satisfying; it’s always rewarding when careful taking different measures; in spite of taking wiring multiple approach routes that fnally translates directly into a clean, lightning-fast user experience is even possible via the infamous and notorious NextJS React stack. #dev","content_html":"<a class=\"tgme_widget_message_reply user-color-default\" href=\"/posts/477\"><blockquote><small>\n<div class=\"tgme_widget_message_author accent_color\">\n  <span class=\"tgme_widget_message_author_name\">Toshiki's Devpedia</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"tgme_widget_message_text js-message_reply_text\">Built another wheel again! I completley rewrote an existing project named BroadCast Channel from scratch. It syncs content from a Telegram channel into a searchable, multilingual static microblog, with support for local media mirroring, RSS, and tag pages.…</div>\n</small></blockquote></a><div class=\"image-list-container\">\n      <img class=\"zoomable\" src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,quality=85/media/4b2c86557886330a1f3373abdac4902d.jpg\" alt=\"Surprisingly, after tightening nearly every corner of the stack from static generation and CDN delivery to image optimization and caching; this actually turned out to be one of the fastest sites I’ve built so far. Seeing the performance audits and SEO scores come out this strong was genuinely satisfying; it’s always rewarding when careful taking different measures; in spite of taking wiring multiple approach routes that fnally translates directly into a clean, lightning-fast user experience is even possible via the infamous and notorious NextJS React stack. #dev\" loading=\"lazy\"></div>Surprisingly, after tightening nearly every corner of the stack from static generation and CDN delivery to image optimization and caching; this actually turned out to be one of the fastest sites I’ve built so far. Seeing the performance audits and SEO scores come out this strong was genuinely satisfying; it’s always rewarding when careful taking different measures; in spite of taking wiring multiple approach routes that fnally translates directly into a clean, lightning-fast user experience is even possible via the infamous and notorious NextJS React stack. <a href=\"/search?q=%23dev\" title=\"#dev\">#dev</a>","tags":["dev"],"date_published":"2026-03-13T12:50:45.000Z"},{"id":"https://tg.toshiki.dev/posts/517","url":"https://tg.toshiki.dev/posts/517","title":"Kawaii me!✌️ #lifeKawaii me!✌️ #life","content_html":"<div class=\"image-list-container\">\n      <img class=\"zoomable\" src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,quality=85/media/13e2ce4314cb80a4c50ed4290d9416c4.jpg\" alt=\"Kawaii me!✌️ #lifeKawaii me!✌️ #life\" loading=\"lazy\">\n      <img class=\"zoomable\" src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,quality=85/media/f4f14c8410280bc5e0ebca8bc5f36783.jpg\" alt=\"Kawaii me!✌️ #lifeKawaii me!✌️ #life\" loading=\"lazy\">\n      <img class=\"zoomable\" src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,quality=85/media/52671236dc5b6eb573d5975e2eb45ddc.jpg\" alt=\"Kawaii me!✌️ #lifeKawaii me!✌️ #life\" loading=\"lazy\"></div><div class=\"tgme_widget_message_text js-message_text\">Kawaii me!<i class=\"emoji\"><b>✌️</b></i> <a href=\"/search?q=%23life\" title=\"#life\">#life</a></div>","tags":["life"],"date_published":"2026-03-13T07:08:30.000Z"},{"id":"https://tg.toshiki.dev/posts/513","url":"https://tg.toshiki.dev/posts/513","title":"📍Bla